ezvcard.util

Class ListMultimap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ezvcard.util.ListMultimap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key
    V - the value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<K,List<V>>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    VCardParameters

    public class ListMultimap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Iterable<Map.Entry<K,List<V>>>
    A multimap that uses ArrayList objects to store its values. The internal Map implementation is a LinkedHashMap.
    Author:
    Michael Angstadt

      • ListMultimap

        public ListMultimap(Map<K,List<V>> map)

        Creates a new multimap backed by the given map. Changes made to the given map will effect the multimap and vice versa.

        To avoid problems, it is highly recommended that the given map NOT be modified by anything other than this ListMultimap class after being passed into this constructor.

        Parameters:
        map - the backing map
